         I have both the 8th shawl and all chardok quest gear, <BR>the chardok quests are WELL worth the effor, although the rares can get you down(no 'feel' of quest progression when wating on 3+ day spawns), and tehres also the perk of banking/buying/sniping in chardok</P><P>of course when i did mine, i had no idea sniping was possible(a fellow mage was doing faction at the same time and the idea of a coh/herbalist coh crew popped into my head)</P><P>now teh shawls on teh other hand, back when FT items were mythical and FT2 was as high as it went, the shawl was godly</P><P>i persnoally started the quest cuz i was unguilded and i could do most of it solo, i made it up to 4th shawl this way, then came tailoring</P><P>mind you, i have an 8th shawl, my tailoring is 137(was 130 when i got my 7th shawl, 7points of dire fur), and my smithing is 141(i had 140 smithing prior to the smithing 'nerf')</P><P>tailoring is the epitome of what NOT to do with tradeskills, it takes COUNTLESS hours of LAME GREENY farming to then spend loads of plat to do combines, to get shitty skill ups, when i quit on tailoring, i was averaging 1point per 1hour of farming, and that was GOOD<BR>now picture getting from 110-160, 40+ hours of FARMING SILK, thats right, just farming</P><P>this is why i stopped at 130, <BR>i had also given up on the shawls when i saw terrorclaws hide, but started again after seeing the 8th shawl(esp since it has hp on it, a good sign of stats to come, im assuming 10th shawl will be 10ac/stats/saves 100hp/mana with an effect that has mana/hp regen as well as foci)</P><P>unfortunately smithing is now VERY similar to tailoring except, ..., expensive</P><P>to get past(i think its like 110) you have to do FS, which is a hassle, and htat only goes to 130-140, at which point your left wiht cultural and the like</P><P>am i happy i have the shawl?, yes</P><P>will i do it again?, no</P><P>will i EVER EVER skill up tailoring/smithing again, hell no, im actually very upset that i got skill ups doing fur padding, it was a principle thing(mind oyu, im ont rich, i only bought like 3 of the furs i used, took me about 20 furs to make my 8th shawl)</P><P>luckilly, given the quest lore, i think the skills are pretty much done on the shawls, 7th shawl was supposed to be the 'final skillful product', they had to pull the 8th shawl out of theyre ass, so its the same shawl, just blessed by brell himself, and hte text for the 8th shawl says the following steps will be an assault on kael itself(including oldworld shorties, lol), so hopfeully 9th/10th shawl will be more like 9th/10th rings, which is kind of shitty for the pure skill questers out there, trade skills(read: tailoring/smithing) are NOT fun, theyre not luctrative(well, mebee smihting if you got your 242 pre-nerf , post new cultural)</P><P>so to in a nut shell, <BR>if your asking "shawls.. how much time?" the asnwer for you is, "too fucking long"</P><P>Kriista Silence<BR>Warlock of Veeshan</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
