        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I have the 8th shawl and frankly would like to disagree with a lot of the people here who've recommended against doing it.  It's about pacing.  Don't try to get it all done at once.  This is the type of quest that can really help with downtime.  Work on tailoring or other skills when things are slow.  Since you don't go backwards in your skills, you'll always be looking forward.  I've found tailoring to be a skill that makes you tear your hair out, but now that I'm pretty good at it (167 skill), I'm actually beginning to earn some OK cash with it.  I don't do it every day - just when things are slow - but it's nice to have a little income to suppliment other activities :)</P><P>In other words, if you chose to do the shawl - don't consider the item to be the only reward.  It's a symbol of all the other gains you will have made that you can continue to apply.  With the improvements to tradeskills, there are some nice things you can make when you get to the upper levels.  The shawl is a great way to keep yourself motivated in order to get to that point.</P><P>It's not for everyone.  But if you're feeling the urge to try, then why the hell not???</P><P><BR>Takilth Shadowpath<BR>aka Necrotart<BR>Iksar Warlock of the Final Shedding<BR>proud member of Shining Alliance<BR>Prexus<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

